                        <interp inst="t18350817-name-576" type="surname" value="NIFTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350817-name-576" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH NIFTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable D</hi> 118.) I was passing through wo<lb></lb>burn-place, about four o'clock—I saw some persons—I went up, and a gentleman had the prisoner by the collar, and this shawl—I took him to the prosecutrix's shop—I then took him to the station—he asked me what I thought the Magistrate would do with him—I said, I did not know—he said he had found the shawl—I said that could not be the case for a gen<lb></lb>tleman on horseback had pursued him—he then said, it was his first of<lb></lb>fence, and he hoped he should not be sent to Newgate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I was going along; three boys rushed out of the shop, and dropped the shawl; I took it up.</p>
